21template <class Next>
22class StackCheckLoweringReducer : public Next {
23 public:
24 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(StackCheckLowering)
25
26 OpIndex REDUCE(StackCheck)(StackCheckOp::Kind kind) {
27#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
28 if (kind == StackCheckOp::Kind::kWasmFunctionHeader &&
29 __ IsLeafFunction()) {
30 return OpIndex::Invalid();
31 }
32#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
33 // Loads of the stack limit should not be load-eliminated as it can be
34 // modified by another thread.
35 V<WordPtr> limit = __ Load(
36 __ LoadRootRegister(), LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().NotLoadEliminable(),
37 MemoryRepresentation::UintPtr(), IsolateData::jslimit_offset());
38 compiler::StackCheckKind check_kind =
39 kind == StackCheckOp::Kind::kJSFunctionHeader
40 ? compiler::StackCheckKind::kJSFunctionEntry
41 : compiler::StackCheckKind::kWasm;
42 V<Word32> check = __ StackPointerGreaterThan(limit, check_kind);
43 IF_NOT (LIKELY(check)) {
44 if (kind == StackCheckOp::Kind::kJSFunctionHeader) {
45 __ CallRuntime_StackGuardWithGap(isolate(), __ NoContextConstant(),
46 __ StackCheckOffset());
47 }
48#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
49 else {
50 DCHECK(kind == StackCheckOp::Kind::kWasmFunctionHeader ||
51 kind == StackCheckOp::Kind::kWasmLoop);
52 // TODO(14108): Cache descriptor.
53 V<WordPtr> builtin =
54 __ RelocatableWasmBuiltinCallTarget(Builtin::kWasmStackGuard);
55 const CallDescriptor* call_descriptor =
56 compiler::Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
57 __ graph_zone(), // zone
58 NoContextDescriptor{}, // descriptor
59 0, // stack parameter count
60 CallDescriptor::kNoFlags, // flags
61 Operator::kNoProperties, // properties
62 StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub); // stub call mode
63 const TSCallDescriptor* ts_call_descriptor = TSCallDescriptor::Create(
64 call_descriptor, compiler::CanThrow::kNo, __ graph_zone());
65 // Pass custom effects to the `Call` node to mark it as non-writing.
66 __ Call(builtin, {}, ts_call_descriptor,
67 OpEffects()
68 .CanReadMemory()
69 .RequiredWhenUnused()
70 .CanCreateIdentity());
71 }
72#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
73 }
74
75 return OpIndex::Invalid();
76 }
77
78 OpIndex REDUCE(JSLoopStackCheck)(V<Context> context,
79 V<FrameState> frame_state) {
80 V<Word32> limit = __ Load(
81 __ ExternalConstant(
82 ExternalReference::address_of_no_heap_write_interrupt_request(
83 isolate())),
84 LoadOp::Kind::RawAligned().NotLoadEliminable(),
85 MemoryRepresentation::Uint8());
86
87 IF_NOT (LIKELY(__ Word32Equal(limit, 0))) {
88 __ CallRuntime_HandleNoHeapWritesInterrupts(isolate(), frame_state,
89 context);
90 }
91
92 return OpIndex::Invalid();
93 }
94
95 private:
96 Isolate* isolate() {
97 if (!isolate_) isolate_ = __ data() -> isolate();
98 return isolate_;
99 }
100
101 Isolate* isolate_ = nullptr;
102};
